President Obama and President Karzai had a one-hour video teleconference where they discussed various topics including the successful Kabul Conference, upcoming Afghan parliamentary elections, renewal of the U.S.-Afghanistan Strategic Partnership Declaration, anti-corruption efforts, civilian casualties, and regional relations. They agreed to continue working together to keep pressure on the Taliban and build Afghan capacity. They also agreed to combat violent extremism, improve governance, deliver basic services, and ensure Afghanistan's stability, security, and prosperity. Ambassador Karl Eikenberry and General David Petraeus also participated in the teleconference.